items.name: Melody Wylde MoC+
items.description:
‚Äº IMPORTANT ‚Äº

  • Your voice matters! Show your support and leave a post, comment and most importantly a review! ‚≠ê

  • Custom LORAs available upon request. Just buymeacoffee.‚òï

  • This is now a + LORA! (details in workflow advice below)

  • üëá(workflow advice below) üëá

üìùBiographyüìù

üåüMelody Wyldeüåü

also known as Sweet X Melody, is a film actress and model born on November 14, 1995, in Yokosuka, Japan. Melody is of mixed ethnicity, with Japanese and Dominican heritage. She stands at 5'4" (163 cm) and weighs around 110 lbs (50 kg), with a slim figure measuring 32AA-24-36. She has dark brown eyes and black hair with purple undertones, and a small tattoo on her center upper back.

Melody began her career in the entertainment industry in 2017 at the age of 22. Melody has performed in videos with other well-known actresses, such as Alana Summers and Carolina Sweets. Melody has won several awards for her performances, including the Streamate Halloween Contest in 2017 and the Beaver Hunt of the Year by Hustler Magazine in 2018.

In her personal life, Melody has a passion for traveling and swimming. She is also a selfie lover and enjoys sharing her experiences on social media. Although there is no information available about her family and relationships, it is known that she is unmarried and does not have any children. Melody is still active in the adult industry and continues to perform in videos and livecam shows. She also has an official website where fans can access her videos and photos.

üí°Workflow Adviceüí°

üîßPrompt and Samplingüîß

  • What's the + for?

    • Just an easy way to indicate the dataset image for this particular LORA was based off a minimum of 1024px+ quality source images with the LORA trained at 1024,1024 (I may go higher in the future if I can get a properly working configuration).

    • For the most part, you can start with higher base resolutions to capture more details and/or generate higher quality outputs. See some of the gallery examples.

    • You don't have to gen at high resolution, low res generations will be better quality as well.

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75 - 1.1.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.üòà

    • Tile pre-sample and model is good for extreme close ups

    • I use segmentation for lots of my generations now.

üóíÔ∏èSide NotesüóíÔ∏è

  • This + series is something new, let me know if I should take the extra time it takes to create these type of LoRAs or just stick with the regular quality.

  • Help me help you: Leave a review if you've used this LORA.

  • Most of my gens are not voodoo or outside of workflows I've indicated here or in my other posts.

    • In other words: Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond with suggestions.

items.name: GI Joe - The Baroness
items.description:
COBRAAAAAAAAAA

I noticed a distinct lack of 80's characters on here and being a Gen-X'er, I had to rectify that issue. To continue the series, I now present the character that is directly responsible for the awakening of many a Gen X femme - The Baroness from GI Joe. This Lora was trained on images from the 1980's Toei Animation cartoon and various cosplays. I did not use images from the live-action movie.

Image was trained on SD1.5, so it is good for most other checkpoints. I would recommend setting the strength to 0.8-1. Highres.fx = VERY YES. I usually go about 1/2 of my initial steps with a denoising strength of 0.3-0.4.

Activation word is "baroness". Good luck, have fun, and stay tuned for more 80's icons!

items.name: rannou75 Style
items.description:
This model is based on anything4.5 trained from the picture of rannou75, and it is recommended to use weights between 0.5 to 0.9.

There have been many controversies about the training and use of art style models, but they are also a difficult part to avoid in the process of AI painting progress.

Therefore, it is recommended to use such art style models as a kind of existence similar to potions, by matching Loras of different art styles with different weights to form images with different styles (although this may lead to bad results, it is worth trying).Alternatively, it can be used to match your favorite character models. Anyway, I hope not to compare it with the artist's own work and make rude remarks, which will harm the community's environment.

At the same time, there are still many problems to be discovered in this model. In short, hope you have a good time.

items.name: KIRIGAMI
items.description:
Kirigami is a traditional Japanese paper-cutting art that combines the techniques of origami (paper folding) and cutting. The word "kirigami" comes from the Japanese words "kiru" meaning "to cut" and "kami" meaning "paper."

In kirigami, intricate and decorative designs are created by folding and cutting a single sheet of paper. Unlike origami, which focuses solely on folding, kirigami allows for the addition of cut-out patterns, creating more complex and detailed designs.

Kirigami designs can range from simple and elegant to highly intricate and elaborate. Common subjects include animals, flowers, buildings, and geometric patterns. The possibilities for creativity and artistic expression are nearly endless.

One of the unique aspects of kirigami is that the cut paper remains connected at certain points, creating a delicate and interconnected structure. This adds an extra dimension to the artwork, as the cut paper can be opened, folded, or displayed in various ways to create dynamic and visually engaging compositions.

Kirigami has applications beyond decorative art. It is often used in architectural design, pop-up books, greeting cards, and even in the creation of complex three-dimensional sculptures. The combination of folding and cutting allows for the creation of intricate and eye-catching designs that bring a sense of movement and depth to the artwork.

Practicing kirigami requires patience, precision, and a steady hand. It is a skill that requires careful attention to detail and the ability to follow complex patterns. However, the results can be truly stunning, showcasing the beauty and intricacy that can be achieved through the combination of folding and cutting paper.

Kirigami continues to be practiced and appreciated as both a traditional craft and a contemporary art form, allowing artists and enthusiasts to explore the interplay between positive and negative space, and to create intricate and visually captivating works of art.

This is my pack of Overwatch Female Characters LoRAs. These LoRAs is trained on NovelAI, so it will not do particularly well with realistic models.

It was trained on Rule34 art. Original outfits may not come through well.

The strength is good from 0.6 to 0.8, but I use 0.7 strength. All images are generated are generated with Hires Fix and the Orangemix VAE. The provided GIF was made with my custom blends. I do not have enough time in the world to test these or provide many preview images, I know the LoRAs work.

Keywords are included in the .zip file, along with a few pieces of advice. Included characters are Ana, Ashe, Brigitte, Junker Queen, Kiriko, Mei, Mercy, Moira, Pharah, Sojourn, Sombra, Symmetra, Tracer, Widowmaker, Zarya, and D.VA

items.name: Katy Perry 2010s Embedding
items.description:
Katheryn Elizabeth Hudson (born October 25, 1984), known professionally as Katy Perry, is an American singer-songwriter and television personality. Known for her influence on modern pop music and her campy style, she has been referred to as the "Queen of Camp" by Vogue. Pursuing a career in gospel music at 16, Perry released her debut album, Katy Hudson, under Red Hill Records in 2001, which was commercially unsuccessful. She moved to Los Angeles at 17 to venture into secular music, and later adopted the stage name "Katy Perry" from her mother's maiden name. She recorded an album while signed to Columbia Records, but was dropped before signing to Capitol Records.

If you like my work and you feel like it, you can invite me to a Ko-fi!

items.name: Hiroi Kikuri (Bocchi the Rock)
items.description:
Model of the perpetually drunk bassist from Bocchi the Rock!

v2 Release

Improved a lot on the finer details and consistency while mostly retaining the flexibility of the prior version.

Also, teeth work a lot better now. You should still use some auxiliary models to improve results, but even out of the box they look pretty decent more regularly now.

v1 Release

Outside of her teeth this seems to be working pretty well. By default the model will somehow avoid teeth altogether, but her usual sharp teeth kind of come off somewhere between noisy and nightmarish. If you're hellbent on including those, choosing a more anime-style or less realistic model and maybe including a LoRA to improve the overall appearance of sharp teeth may help (possibly).

Other than the activation tag, using green dress should work well to add her signature outfit.

This LyCORIS has been trained after carefully selecting 53 images. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!

LyCORIS weights should be between 1-1.4
